@lguohan Some thoughts:
Is this currently the infrastructure code and solves some of the earlier discussed issues during CRUD adaption. Do we have a plan to extend it to other objects. Rather the architecture we have for saiobject.h, which provides common getters and setters based on the object type could be considered for this. 
For example if some application with SW based learning does bulking of say FDB notifications and can do one shot FDB creations.

@itaibaz - We understand that for regular traps. BGP/STP will have only one trap. 
in case of ACL trap
/*\* ACL traps (default packet action is drop) */
-    SAI_HOSTIF_TRAP_TYPE_ACL_MIN = SAI_HOSTIF_TRAP_TYPE_NEIGH_MAX + 1,
     SAI_HOSTIF_TRAP_TYPE_ACL_MAX = SAI_HOSTIF_TRAP_TYPE_ACL_MIN + SAI_HOSTIF_TRAP_TYPE_TABLE_RANGE,

That means i can not create more than 1 ACL trap Id's right? if no,  can you add example to configure multiple ACL traps and use it by application.

@tushar : the behavior is very crisp and clear from a SAI modeling perspective. I would disagree that any of the below binding points are not well defined: 
    - Ports, LAGs, VLANs, Router Interfaces , Tunnel Termination and Tunnel Originations
    - I agree with the definition of bridge interfaces (but that spec is not yet discussed nor the code changes are in the pull request).

