@rivasiv,  In LAG_member, there are EGRESS/INGRESS_DISABLE attribute for individual members. In VLAN_member, there is also tagged mode for each individual member.

In both cases, the member objects do have member specific attribute we need to configure. Then, somewhat we need to find way to expose it. the previous approach is to design another structure, e.g. sai_vlan_port_t, which does not fit well with the SAI API.

